And now for an informed opinion:

The quality is mediocre.  It's slightly better than a widescreen DVD rip.  It is not a digital rip.  I'm not sure how they transferred it, but it is NOT full framerate, which makes fight/action scenes a bit of a blur.

There are hard-overlayed Russian subtitles.

The sound is somewhat flat and distorted, but tolerable.

If you want to watch this on your phone, go for it.  If you want to watch it on your flat screen with surround sound in your living room, wait for the blu-ray rip.
